    "body": "I've just rebased on develop, and I'd like to add a suggestion.\r\n\r\nWe have these events in:\r\n```clojure\r\n;; ns  status-im.contexts.wallet.send.events\r\n(rf/reg-event-fx :wallet/select-send-account-address\r\n (fn [{:keys [db]} [{:keys [address stack-id]}]]\r\n   {:db (-> db\r\n            (assoc-in [:wallet :ui :send :send-account-address] address)\r\n            (update-in [:wallet :ui :send] dissoc :to-address))\r\n    :fx [[:navigate-to-within-stack [:wallet-select-asset stack-id]]]}))\r\n\r\n(rf/reg-event-fx :wallet/select-send-address\r\n (fn [{:keys [db]} [{:keys [address stack-id]}]]\r\n   {:db (-> db\r\n            (assoc-in [:wallet :ui :send :to-address] address)\r\n            (update-in [:wallet :ui :send] dissoc :send-account-address))\r\n    :fx [[:navigate-to-within-stack [:wallet-select-asset stack-id]]]}))\r\n```\r\n\r\nI think `:wallet/select-send-account-address` was initially created, they are almost the same, to avoid duplicating subscriptions to get the `:to-address` account and the `:send-account-address`, I believe is better to just use one of them (`:wallet/select-send-account-address`) and remove the other one and its usages.\r\n\r\n(I did that change in my branch, pretty small but important).\r\n\r\nThe other changes are related to set up the data for the page, so nothing else to add.\r\n",
